Brandon Shores has another 30% aqueous ammonia tank that supplies ammonia for pH control for the boiler feed water (cycle chemistry process). This tank has a capacity of 5,000 gallons. It is surrounded by a dike that drains directly into a 70,000 gallon sump located under the storage tank.



Release Prevention Policies



Raven believes that safety and health are of utmost importance and that all injuries and most illnesses are preventable. Operating safely, with a constant focus on accident prevention and occupational health processes, is the most efficient way to manage our business. It is the best way to safeguard our employees and the communities in which we are located. Our safety concern extends not only to that of our fellow employees, but also to our families, customers, contractors, visitors, and communities in which we operate.



Raven utilizes effective accident prevention strategies such as safety in engineering design, training, behavior-based initiatives, and administrative controls to safeguard against workplace hazards. We have a comprehensive accidental release prevention program based on the following key elements:



- Hazard review - A detailed hazard analysis was performed identifying risks and recommendations for reducing the potential for and impact of releases. All design recommendations have been incorporated.

